def: Passing or flowing through a bridge; -- said of water. Wright.
Beneath the endoskeleton; hypaxial; as, the hyposkeletalmuscles; -- opposed to episkeletal.

To separate, select, or pick out; to choose and gather orcollect; as, to cuil flowers.From his herd he culls, For slaughter, from the fairest of his bulls.Dryden.Whitest honey in fairy gardens culled. Tennyson.
One whose intention is good. "Well-meaners think no harm."Dryden.
Want of parallelism between one series of strata and another,especially when due to a disturbance of the position of the earlierstrata before the latter were deposited.
A lampoon or satirical writing. Macaulay.
